transcript.text: Hello everyone, and welcome back to our order management tutorial series.
Whether you need to make changes to a customer's order or update the details on Print Shop makes it easy to do so.
In this video, we'll walk you through the simple steps to modify an order and make payment requests efficiently.
So let's get started.
In the admin panel, navigate to the Order section and go to the list Orders.
From the order listing, select the order that you need to modify.
Click on the Actions drop down and select the Modify Order option.
On the Modify Order screen, you can verify the customer details along with the shipping billing addresses and payment shipping details.
On the later part of the screen, you can see the order product details.
With the Modify design.
You can choose a different product design from the customer's My Saved Designs or choose to redesign the product.
We can learn more about the modified design from our order management video.

Moving forward to product detail modifications, you can change the product size using the edit icon, add the product SKU, change the attribute selections for the available product options, or even add new product options.
For adding the pricing of the modifications, you can take the help of the price calculator to check the price and enter the price difference in the fields provided.
To change the shipping details and charges, click on the Calculate Shipping Rate.
Select the shipping method and click on Save from the top of the screen for recalculating the tax rates.
Click on Calculate Tax to view the updated tax and then save.
You can add any reward points or coupon codes for this order to offer discounted prices.
The reason for order modification can be mentioned using the predefined comment section along with an option to notify the customer about the modifications.
Apart from modifying the existing ordered product, you can add a new product to the existing order using the Add New Order Product button.
The steps are the same as adding an offline order.
To learn more about adding an offline order, you can refer to the Help portal.
Now the question is how you will get payment for the difference amount or for the new product added to the order.
The answer is through the payment request.
To request payment, click on the Payment request from the left navigation panel.
On the Payment request screen, you need to 1st enter and select the Order ID.
You can see the payment and customer details of the order ID details below.
Enter the amount for which you are generating the request.
Based on the modifications.
If the order due date will be affected, you can choose to recalculate the order due date and enter the remarks or comments.
Select what will be the next order status and payment status after the customer makes the payment through this request.
Once done with all the relevant details, click on Save.
You can find the new request added in the Race tab with options to cancel, modify the request, mark it as paid, or send a reminder to the customer.
You can also manage the reminder e-mail content from the automatic e-mail reminder under the Content Management section Ino moving to the next tab.
Once the customer has made the payment, the request will be displayed under the Completed tab.
You can verify the payment details along with the remarks.
If the customer has rejected the payment request, it will fall under the Cancel tab.
You can check the remarks and other details with the delete option.
All the payment requests that are to be raised for future transactions will appear here.
This is mainly related to the partial payment method in the stand alone tab.
The failed payments through online mediums will appear here with the error details.
This is how you can modify the order and create payment requests from the admin panel.
If you have any questions, our support executives are here to help.
Just reach out through live chat on onprintshop.com.
Thanks for tuning in.
